Attributions
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

MatrixNet interoperates with, and builds upon, the following third-party and
system technologies. Their use does not imply any endorsement by their
respective authors.

- libpcap / tcpdump
  MatrixNet reads packets through the BPF / PKTAP interfaces and uses the pcapng
  capture file format pioneered by these projects for interoperability with
  Wireshark and other analysis tools.
  https://www.tcpdump.org

- Wireshark
  The pcapng files MatrixNet exports are designed to be opened in Wireshark.
  https://www.wireshark.org

- Apple system frameworks and interfaces
  MatrixNet relies on macOS system facilities, including the NetworkStatistics
  framework (the kernel connection-attribution mechanism used by nettop and
  Activity Monitor), the BPF / PKTAP packet-capture interfaces, ServiceManagement
  (SMAppService) for privileged helper registration, and XPC for inter-process
  communication. These are property of Apple Inc.

Additional third-party components bundled with MatrixNet (for example, a local
GeoIP database and any open-source dependencies) are listed, together with their
respective licenses, in the application's About / acknowledgements view and the
source tree as they are introduced.
